texts.value: Catalyzes the irreversible transamination of the L-tryptophan metabolite L-kynurenine to form kynurenic acid (KA). As a member of the malate-aspartate shuttle, it has a key role in the intracellular NAD(H) redox balance. Is important for metabolite exchange between mitochondria and cytosol, and for amino acid metabolism. Facilitates cellular uptake of long-chain free fatty acids
In eukaryotes there are cytoplasmic, mitochondrial and chloroplastic isozymes
Belongs to the class-I pyridoxal-phosphate-dependent aminotransferase family
